00:16:43,860 --> 00:16:51,380
Soup, bread, a pair. The note had three words in her round motherly hand. Eat for the little one.

194
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:57,620
She knew. Of course she knew. Donna Kira knew everything in that house. I ate the whole bowl of

195
00:16:57,620 --> 00:17:03,740
soup without tasting it. I ate the bread. I ate the pair down to the core. It was the first thing I did for

196
00:17:03,740 --> 00:17:09,720
the little one. And the second thing I did for myself. In Arena called near five, I answered because it was

197
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:16,980
her. Are you alive? I am. Are you eating? Now I am. You want me to come over? I thought a second.

198
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:22,420
The idea of having someone in the room felt too big to bear. Like a strong light in an eye used to the

199
00:17:22,420 --> 00:17:29,200
dark. Not today. Tomorrow. Tomorrow I'll say. She was silent long enough for me to know. She was thinking

200
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:34,320
about not hanging up. And then she said her thing. If you need wine and a butter knife,

201
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:41,440
