00:19:25,060 --> 00:19:29,900
Bring them to me. He stood still half a second, enough to register that I wasn't asking.

222
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:35,300
And left without a single question. I opened the drawer of my father's study and took out

223
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:39,540
something that had sat there for three months. The handwritten draft of the clause.

224
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:45,220
Yellowed paper, black ink, my writing. I set it on the desk and looked at it the way one looks at

225
00:19:45,220 --> 00:19:49,560
a dead animal he hadn't the courage to bury when he should have. There was a promise I'd made

226
00:19:49,560 --> 00:19:54,900
my own conscience three months ago. On the morning I Orlando had agreed to sleep at my side without

