275
00:24:31,560 --> 00:24:38,400
inside her. Bastion waited in the car, outside. He didn't ask a question. He just opened the rear door

276
00:24:38,400 --> 00:24:43,760
and kept looking straight ahead while I got in. The radio was low, an old Italian song I knew

277
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:50,520
without remembering from where. Cafe Vecchi Aroma, I said, buckling the belt, then the runnyeri office.

278
00:24:51,040 --> 00:24:55,860
Then an address I'll give you later. He nodded half a millimeter with his head. Started the car.

279
00:24:56,280 --> 00:25:00,540
The drive to the old neighborhood took long enough for me to count my breaths. We passed the

280
00:25:00,540 --> 00:25:06,060
intersection where, months before, a collector had shown up at my apartment door with a Manila envelope

