287
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:49,800
back. A white-haired woman reading a newspaper. I sat at the window table. The table. The one where he'd

288
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:55,200
sat on the late afternoon of a Thursday that now seemed to belong to another life. His chair was

289
00:25:55,200 --> 00:26:01,740
empty across for me. And even empty, it seemed occupied. The waiter came slowly. He was a thin man,

290
00:26:01,740 --> 00:26:07,120
clean apron. With that look of someone who'd worked in an old cafe since he was 15 and would never

291
00:26:07,120 --> 00:26:13,580
